<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>6-751.07</num>
  <heading>Permits.</heading>
  <text>No owner may permanently wire a smoke detector to the electrical system of a structure without first obtaining an electrical permit from the Permit Division of the Department of Licenses, Investigation and Inspections.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 2-81" type="History" path="§8">June 20, 1978, D.C. Law 2-81, § 8, 24 DCR 9050</annotation>
